

Object Oriented Programming:
    In OOP, there are set of objects that interact with each other
    to solve a problem.

    Paradigm which allows us to solve problems with the help of
    objects which represents the real world entities.


CLASSES & OBJECTS:
    > Class is a blueprint or template
    > Objects are the real thing
    > YOu create objects in your program and they interact with
    each other to complete the work

DESIGN A CLASS:
    * Properties or Fields (Object knows)
    * Methods (Object Does)